name: Carnival Row
overview: In a mystical and dark city filled with humans, fairies and other creatures, a police detective investigates a series of gruesome murders leveled against the fairy population. During his investigation, the detective becomes the prime suspect and must find the real killer to clear his name.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: With a serial killer loose on Carnival Row, and a government that turns a blind eye to the deaths of its lower class citizens, Rycroft Philostrate, a war-hardened investigator, is the only person willing to stop the murders and maintain the fragile peace. But when Vignette Stonemoss, a faerie refugee, turns up in the Burgue, she forces Philo to reckon with a past he's tried to forget.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Love. Murder. Conspiracy. Revolution. When mysterious killings inflame tensions between the Faefolk and their Human oppressors, each denizen of Carnival Row must choose who they are and how to act.

episodes.name: Some Dark God Wakes
episodes.overview: Rycroft “Philo” Philostrate investigates “Unseelie Jack”, a mysterious assailant with a grudge against the fae. Vignette Stonemoss barely escapes Tirnanoc with her life and arrives in The Burgue looking for a fresh start. Imogen Spurnrose meets her new neighbor. In Parliament, the fight over the critch heats up.

episodes.name: Aisling
episodes.overview: Philo investigates the murder of a mysterious fae. Tourmaline introduces Vignette to a new group of faeries. Imogen tries to have Agreus removed from the neighborhood. Jonah disappears.

episodes.name: Kingdoms of the Moon
episodes.overview: Once, as a Burguish soldier, Philo was tasked with protecting a faerish mimasery. While The Pact bears down on them, Philo meets Vignette and finds love in the most unlikely of places.

episodes.name: The Joining of Unlike Things
episodes.overview: Philo investigates the murder of his childhood headmaster. Vignette ingratiates herself into the Black Raven. Imogen hatches a plan to help her brother. Breakspear goes on the offensive with Longerbane.

episodes.name: Grieve No More
episodes.overview: Philo consults a Haruspex in an effort to find clues about the killer. Vignette grows closer with her newfound family. Upon Jonah’s return home, his parents cast a more watchful eye over him as a new player makes a splash in Parliament. Imogen brings Agreus into her circle.

episodes.name: Unaccompanied Fae
episodes.overview: The pieces of the puzzle start to come together for Philo. Vignette finds home in a place she never expected. Jonah sneaks off to see someone he shouldn’t. Imogen and Agreus step out together in public.

episodes.name: The World to Come
episodes.overview: Because he withheld evidence from his fellow detectives, Philo is accused of being the man behind the string of murders and is thrown in jail. There, he finds some unexpected help from Vignette. Elsewhere, Ezra takes exception to Imogen’s relationship with Agreus. Sophie offers Jonah a deal.

episodes.name: The Gloaming
episodes.overview: As tensions rise on Carnival Row, Philo must confront both darkness incarnate and the evil that controls it. Vignette gleans the true nature of The Burgue. Imogen lets her feelings for Agreus go unbridled. Breakspear's secrets catch up to him.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: With a serial killer loose on Carnival Row, and a government that turns a blind eye to the deaths of its lower class citizens, Rycroft Philostrate, a war-hardened investigator, is the only person willing to stop the murders and maintain the fragile peace. But when Vignette Stonemoss, a faerie refugee, turns up in the Burgue, she forces Philo to reckon with a past he's tried to forget.

episodes.name: Fight or Flight
episodes.overview: Lovers Philo and Vignette risk their lives to help the oppressed Faefolk of Carnival Row.

episodes.name: New Dawn
episodes.overview: When Philo plots to challenge Jonah's hereditary claim to the Chancellorship, Vignette intervenes.

episodes.name: The Martyr's Hand
episodes.overview: While Philo investigates the murders of the Black Raven’s leaders, Vignette plots revenge.

episodes.name: An Unkindness of Ravens
episodes.overview: Philo races to stop Vignette’s revenge before the Black Raven spark even worse violence.

episodes.name: Reckoning
episodes.overview: Philo plots Vignette’s rescue with an unlikely ally.  Jonah discovers Sophie’s treachery.  The murderer strikes again.

episodes.name: Original Sins
episodes.overview: A painful truth haunts Philo as Carnival Row faces reprisals for the horrific events at Bleakness Keep.

episodes.name: Kindred
episodes.overview: Torn between his Human and Fae sides, Philo makes a choice.

episodes.name: Facta Non Verba
episodes.overview: Reeling from the consequences of his choices, Philo rejects defining himself as either Human or Fae.

episodes.name: Battle Lines
episodes.overview: Justice later through peace, or now through blood?
